The Taliban did not ascend to power in Afghanistan immediately following the Soviet invasion. Instead, the country was governed by the Mujahideens from 1992 to 1996 ( Burhan ud din Rabbani was the president) . In 1994, Taliban wasn't even in power to Ban cricket.

A significant factor influencing the Taliban's stance on sports, particularly cricket, was their Pashtun Nationalist Islamic orientation. Cricket, being predominantly played by Pashtuns, was not prohibited by the Taliban, as they identified with Pashtun cultural and nationalist sentiments. Conversely, football in Afghanistan has been and continues to be dominated by Persian speakers. Despite over 50 percent of Afghans speaking Farsi, the Afghan national cricket team has had a scarcity of Hazara or Tajik players, reflecting the ethnic dynamics within the country.

Certainly! Indian cricket has a rich and storied history, and as of my last knowledge update in January 2022, here is some general information:

Indian Cricket Team:

The Indian national cricket team is governed by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI).
The team is a full member of the International Cricket Council (ICC).
The Indian cricket team is one of the most successful teams in international cricket.
Domestic Cricket:

The structure of domestic cricket in India includes various tournaments like the Ranji Trophy (first-class), Duleep Trophy (first-class), Vijay Hazare Trophy (List A), Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy (T20), and the Indian Premier League (IPL).
Notable Players:

India has produced many legendary cricketers over the years, including Sachin Tendulkar, Rahul Dravid, Sourav Ganguly, Virender Sehwag, Anil Kumble, and more.
International Achievements:

India won its first Cricket World Cup in 1983 under the captaincy of Kapil Dev.
India won the ICC T20 World Cup in 2007 under the captaincy of MS Dhoni.
The Indian cricket team has consistently performed well in Test, One Day International (ODI), and T20 formats.
Indian Premier League (IPL):

The IPL is a professional Twenty20 cricket league in India.
It has gained immense popularity both in India and globally, featuring franchise teams representing different cities.
Top international and Indian players participate in the IPL, making it one of the most-watched and lucrative cricket leagues in the world.
Recent Developments:

Virat Kohli has been a prominent figure in Indian cricket and served as the captain of the Indian cricket team across formats.
Ravi Shastri was the head coach of the Indian cricket team, and the coaching staff has seen changes over the years.
Please note that developments in the world of cricket can happen rapidly, so it's a good idea to check the latest sources for the most up-to-date information.
